Step 18: van_corput_inequality [Lean 4]
Status: [SORRY in Lean 4 — lean/VanCorput.lean]
Claim:
  r₄(N) ≤ 2 · √(N · r₃(N)).
  In Lean 4 (currently sorry'd):
    theorem van_corput_inequality (N : ℕ) :
      rk 4 N ≤ 2 * Nat.sqrt (N * rk 3 N)
Dependencies: Steps 9-13 (all van Corput steps)
Proof:
  WHAT NEEDS TO BE DONE FOR A COMPLETE LEAN PROOF:
  (a) Resolution of Conjecture 2 (Step 12): Step 3 of Lemma 1.1 requires that
      some A_{d*} with size ≥ M²/(4N) is fully 3-AP-free. This is unproved.
  (b) Bijection bookkeeping (Step 9): Formalizing the bijection between 4-APs in A
      and step-d 3-APs in A_{d} requires careful Finset bookkeeping in Lean 4,
      particularly for the additive energy identity Λ₄(A) = Σ_d Λ₃^(d)(A_d).
  (c) Monotonicity of rk 3: Using rk_mono_N to bound |A_{d*}| ≤ rk 3 N (since
      A_{d*} ⊆ {1,...,N-d*} ⊆ {1,...,N}).

  PROOF SKETCH (given Conjecture 2):
    Let A ⊆ range N be 4-AP-free with A.card = m.
    (i) Apply Lemma 1.1 (Steps 9-13) to get d* with |A_{d*}| ≥ m²/(4N) and
        A_{d*} fully 3-AP-free (Conjecture 2).
    (ii) |A_{d*}| ≤ rk 3 N.
    (iii) m²/(4N) ≤ rk 3 N → m² ≤ 4N·rk 3 N → m ≤ Nat.sqrt(4N·rk 3 N).
    (iv) Nat.sqrt(4N·rk 3 N) ≤ 2·Nat.sqrt(N·rk 3 N) by Nat.sqrt_mul_self or similar.
    The sorry is removed once: (a) Conjecture 2 is proved, and (b) the Lean
    bookkeeping in (iii)-(iv) is completed (a routine but tedious Lean exercise).
QED [SORRY in Lean 4].

