Step 26: Proposition 1 — Stronger Freeness for Popular Fibers
Status: [FULLY PROVED — all three conditions in Lean 4, zero sorry; commit f676e3b]
Claim:
  (Proposition 1) Let A ⊆ {0,...,N-1} be 4-AP-free with |A| = M ≥ 2. Then there
  exists d ∈ {1,...,N-1} such that simultaneously:
    (1) |A_d| ≥ M²/(4N)   [size bound — proved by pigeonhole, Step 10; Lean: exists_popular_diff, commit f676e3b]
    (2) A_d has no 3-AP with common difference d    [proved, Step 9]
    (3) A_d has no 3-AP with common difference 2d   [proved, new — see below]

  In Lean 4 (lean/VanCorput.lean):
    theorem proposition_1 (A : Finset ℕ) (N : ℕ) (hN : 0 < N)
        (hAN : A ⊆ Finset.range N) (hA : ¬ HasKAP A 4) (hM : 2 ≤ A.card) :
        ∃ d : ℕ, 0 < d ∧
        A.card ^ 2 ≤ 4 * N * (fiberAtDiff A d).card ∧
        (∀ x, ¬(x ∈ fiberAtDiff A d ∧ x+d ∈ fiberAtDiff A d ∧ x+2*d ∈ fiberAtDiff A d)) ∧
        (∀ x, ¬(x ∈ fiberAtDiff A d ∧ x+2*d ∈ fiberAtDiff A d ∧ x+4*d ∈ fiberAtDiff A d))
  Proof: all three conditions proved in Lean 4 with zero sorry (commit f676e3b).
  Condition (1) closed by exists_popular_diff (6-step Finset proof: Finset.offDiag_card +
  zify/nlinarith + Finset.card_bij + Finset.exists_le_of_sum_le).

Dependencies: Steps 9, 10, 11; Lean 4: van_corput_fiber_step_d_apfree,
              van_corput_fiber_step_2d_apfree (commit 95092b2), exists_popular_diff (PROVED — commit f676e3b)
Proof:
  NEW RESULT — Step-2d freeness of A_d (Lean lemma van_corput_fiber_step_2d_apfree):

  Suppose x, x+2d, x+4d ∈ A_d. Then from the first TWO memberships:
    • x ∈ A_d  ⟹  x ∈ A  AND  x+d ∈ A.
    • x+2d ∈ A_d  ⟹  x+2d ∈ A  AND  (x+2d)+d = x+3d ∈ A.
  Combining: {x, x+d, x+2d, x+3d} ⊆ A — a 4-AP with step d. Contradiction! □
  (Note: the third membership x+4d ∈ A_d is NOT needed. The proof uses only x and x+2d.)

  SAME 4-AP AS STEP-d CASE: Both the step-d proof (Step 9) and this step-2d proof
  derive the SAME 4-AP {x, x+d, x+2d, x+3d} ⊆ A. The two cases are structurally
  identical, differing only in which elements of A_d are assumed.

  LEAN 4 PROOF (van_corput_fiber_step_2d_apfree):
    intro x ⟨hx, hx2d, _⟩  -- ignore the third membership x+4d ∈ A_d
    apply hA
    simp only [fiberAtDiff, Finset.mem_filter] at hx hx2d
    obtain ⟨h0, h1⟩ := hx      -- h0: x ∈ A,   h1: x+d ∈ A
    obtain ⟨h2, h3'⟩ := hx2d   -- h2: x+2d ∈ A, h3': (x+2d)+d ∈ A
    have h3 : x + 3*d ∈ A := by rwa [show (x+2*d)+d = x+3*d from by ring] at h3'
    refine ⟨(Finset.range 4).image (fun i => x + i*d), ?_, x, d, hd, rfl⟩
    -- 4-AP membership: interval_cases i gives i ∈ {0,1,2,3}
    ... simpa using h0/h1/h2/h3 for each i. □

  PROPOSITION 1 PROOF (in Lean):
    obtain ⟨d, hd_pos, hd_size⟩ := exists_popular_diff A N hN hAN hM  -- size bound [PROVED — commit f676e3b]
    exact ⟨d, hd_pos, hd_size,
           van_corput_fiber_step_d_apfree A hA d hd_pos,    -- condition (2) [proved]
           van_corput_fiber_step_2d_apfree A hA d hd_pos⟩  -- condition (3) [proved]
QED [FULLY PROVED — all three conditions in Lean 4 with zero sorry; commit f676e3b].
  exists_popular_diff closed condition (1); van_corput_fiber_step_d_apfree and
  van_corput_fiber_step_2d_apfree close conditions (2) and (3).

