Step 27: 2×3 Grid Reformulation — A_d is 3-AP-free ↔ G(d) = 0
Status: [PROVED — definitional, given Steps 9 and 26]
Claim:
  Define the G-function (2×3 grid count):
    G(A, d) = #{(x,e) : x,x+e,x+2e ∈ A_d,  e > 0,  e ≠ d,  e ≠ 2d}.
  Equivalently (unfolding A_d = {a ∈ A : a+d ∈ A}):
    G(A, d) = #{(x,e) : x,x+e,x+2e ∈ A  AND  x+d,x+e+d,x+2e+d ∈ A,  e > 0, e ≠ d, e ≠ 2d}.
  This counts "2×3 grids" in A with column-difference d and row-step e ∉ {0,d,2d}.

  In Lean 4 (lean/VanCorput.lean):
    noncomputable def G (A : Finset ℕ) (d N : ℕ) : ℕ :=
      ((fiberAtDiff A d ×ˢ Finset.Icc 1 N).filter
        (fun p => p.2 ≠ d ∧ p.2 ≠ 2 * d ∧
                  p.1 + p.2 ∈ fiberAtDiff A d ∧
                  p.1 + 2 * p.2 ∈ fiberAtDiff A d)).card

  **Key equivalence** (given Steps 9 and 26):
    A_d is fully 3-AP-free  ↔  G(A, d) = 0.

Dependencies: Steps 9 (step-d freeness), 11(c)(d) (step-2d freeness), 26 (Prop. 1);
              definition of G
Proof:
  (⟹) If A_d is fully 3-AP-free, then no (x,e) with x,x+e,x+2e ∈ A_d and e > 0 exists.
  In particular G(A, d) = 0 (the filtered set is empty).

  (⟸) Suppose G(A, d) = 0. We show A_d is fully 3-AP-free.
  Suppose for contradiction that (x, x+e, x+2e) ⊆ A_d with e > 0. Then:
    • If e = d: excluded by van_corput_fiber_step_d_apfree (Step 9). ✓
    • If e = 2d: excluded by van_corput_fiber_step_2d_apfree (Step 26). ✓
    • If e ≠ d and e ≠ 2d: then (x, e) ∈ G(A, d), contradicting G = 0. ✓
  (For negative steps, note: if A_d contains a 3-AP (x, x+e, x+2e), reading it backwards
  gives (x+2e, x+e, x) — a 3-AP with positive step 2e, x+e, 0... Actually in our ℕ
  setting, 3-APs are counted with positive step e. For the reversed direction:
    • Step -d ≡ step d in the opposite order: excluded by step-d freeness.
    • Step -2d: if a, a-2d, a-4d ∈ A_d, set x = a-4d, then x, x+2d, x+4d ∈ A_d —
      step-2d 3-AP, excluded by Step 26. ✓
  Hence A_d is free of all 3-APs. □

  NOTE ON THE LEAN DEFINITION: The Lean def uses e ∈ Finset.Icc 1 N (positive steps
  up to N). This suffices since all elements of A_d are < N, so any 3-AP step e in
  A_d satisfies e < N. The conditions e ≠ d and e ≠ 2*d exclude the handled steps.
  For e = 3d, 4d, ..., the cross-term 3-AP would be counted by G if present.
QED [PROVED].

